Homework 12

1)	Selectors in java script, practice by it an example? 

•	document.getElemenById: it will select one element with matching Id name. For example: 
<h1 id=This is Heading 1>Old Header</h1>
<script>
var element = document.getElementById(“This is Heading 1”);
element.innerHTML = “This is New Heading”;
</script>
In this example, “This is Heading 1” will be change to “This is New Heading” by using the id element. 

•	document.getElementByClassName: this method will select all elements with matching classname. For example:
<div class="example">First div element with class="example"</div>
<script>
var x= document.getElementClassName(“example”);
x.innerHTML = “I am a new Div”
</script>
In this example, “First div element with class” will be change to “I am a new Div” by using the classname element. 

•	document.getElementByTagName: this method will select all elements with matching tagnames. For example:
<span>This is span 1</span>
<span>This is span 2</span>
<script>
document.getElementTagName(“span”)
</script>
In this example, all the span 1 and 2 elements will be selected by using the tag name. 

•	document.querySelectorAll: this method will select most of the CSS selectors and most of the selectors will work. For example:

<span>This is span 3</span>
<span>This is span 4</span>
<script>
document.querySelectorAll (“span”)
</script>
In this example, all the span elements will be selected by using query selector all. 


